Some provinces are all blue (SNP & PC), some are all green (Green Party) and some are fence sitters (Liberal). Alberta is a central-western province where our focus is the oil industry, so as a result, our government streamlines great quality of life through oil revenues. Likewise, Alberta is one of, if not the most fiscally corrupt province in the country, we also have the dirtiest air quality. Housing is evidently cheap due to low-priced oil and everyone spends $25,000 on a used pick up truck.

Regrettably, there isn't much to do outside of growing up in Calgary, but really make it out in the real world. 6 months into grad school now and I am making my way across North America and the Trans-atlantic to cultivate a new paradigm and career.

In terms of transitioning, I've lived at home for essentially my indefinite future.
